subsection.def:
candidate (候選人)
                means a candidate who is determined to be validly nominated under section
                    17;

Chief Electoral Officer (總選舉事務主任) means the Chief Electoral Officer
                appointed under section 9 of the Electoral Affairs Commission Ordinance
                    (Cap. 541);

EAC Regulations (《選管會規例》) means regulations made under section 7 of the
                Electoral Affairs Commission Ordinance (Cap.
                541);

Electoral Affairs Commission (選舉管理委員會) means the Electoral Affairs Commission
                established by section 3 of the Electoral Affairs Commission Ordinance
                    (Cap. 541);

member of the Election Committee
                    (選舉委員) means a person whose name appears in
                the final register of members of the Election Committee;

paragraph.content:
The Ombudsman and the holder of any appointment under section
                            6 of The Ombudsman Ordinance (Cap.
                            397);

the Chairperson of the Equal Opportunities Commission and any person
                        employed or whose services are engaged by the Commission under the Sex
                        Discrimination Ordinance (Cap. 480);

any person holding an office, whether permanent or temporary, in a
                        Government department or bureau and employed in the department or
                        bureau;

he is a judicial officer as defined by section 2 of the Judicial
                    Officers Recommendation Commission Ordinance (Cap.
                        92);

subparagraph.content:
any entry permit issued by an authority in any part of the People’s
                        Republic of China which authorizes its holder to enter any part of the
                        People’s Republic of China;

in Hong Kong or any other place, of an offence for which the person has
                        been sentenced to imprisonment, whether suspended or not, for a term
                        exceeding 3 months without the option of a fine;

paragraph.content:
the person has vacated an office, or has been disqualified from entering on
                    an office, under the law, for declining or neglecting to take a specified oath;
                    or

a candidate does not satisfy the requirement in section 13(a),
                    (b), (c) or
                    (d);

is in breach of an oath taken under section 42A of the Schedule;
                    or (Added 14 of 2021 s.
                        397)

subsection.def:
corrupt conduct (舞弊行為) means corrupt conduct within the meaning of Part 2 of
                the Elections (Corrupt and Illegal Conduct) Ordinance (Cap.
                    554);

functional constituency (功能界別) means a functional constituency
                        specified in section 20(1) of the Legislative Council Ordinance
                            (Cap. 542);

Member (議員),
                        in relation to the Legislative Council, has the meaning assigned to it by
                            section 3(1) of the Legislative Council Ordinance (Cap. 542);

officer (高級人員), in relation to a body corporate, includes a director or
                        executive, or any other person concerned in the management, of the
                        body;

registered (登記), in relation to a functional constituency or geographical
                        constituency, means registered under the Legislative Council Ordinance (Cap. 542) as an elector for the
                        constituency;

subsector (界別分組) means, subject to section 11, a subsector
                        represented on the Election Committee as provided by section
                        2(4);

gale warning (烈風警告) has the same meaning as in the Judicial Proceedings
                        (Adjournment During Gale Warnings) Ordinance (Cap.
                            62);

